<tr id="L301"><td><a href="#L301">301</a></td><td>SARGON [OC]:  I am pleased, my beloved. It is good you have found the truth yourself.</td></tr>

<tr id="L302"><td><a href="#L302">302</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Sargon? Where are you? I thought you destroyed by Henoch.</td></tr>

<tr id="L303"><td><a href="#L303">303</a></td><td>SARGON:  I have power even Henoch does not suspect, beloved.</td></tr>

<tr id="L304"><td><a href="#L304">304</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Yes. Yes, I see. I understand. Just as we would have placed our consciousness within robots, Sargon has placed his into your vessel.</td></tr>

<tr id="L305"><td><a href="#L305">305</a></td><td>CHAPEL:  Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L306"><td><a href="#L306">306</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Doctor, leave us. Sargon has a plan. We have much work to do.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--McCoy's office</td></tr>
<tr id="L307"><td><a href="#L307">307</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: McCoy leaves the room, and the door shuts and locks behind him. The ship shakes as he activates his desk monitor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L308"><td><a href="#L308">308</a></td><td>MCCOY:  This is Sickbay. Get me</td></tr>

<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The door opens, and Chapel walks out, staring blankly ahead.</td></tr>

<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Nurse Chapel, what in the devil?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He goes back into the ward.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim? Are you all right?</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, I'm fine, Bones.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Thalassa?</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>MULHALL:  She is now with Sargon, Doctor. I'm Ann Mulhall, back in my own body.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Then we see the three blackened and broken spheres.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim, the receptacles. Spock's consciousness was in one of them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>KIRK:  It was necessary.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What are you talking about? There is no Spock to return to his body. You've killed a loyal officer, your best friend.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>KIRK:  Bones, prepare a hypo. The fastest, deadliest poison to Vulcans. Spock's consciousness is gone. We must kill his body, the thing in it.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Uhura is screaming in terror before collapsing across her console. Chapel is standing rigid by the Captain's chair.</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Must I make an example of you, too, Helm?</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk, Mulhall and McCoy enter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Pain, Captain. And you, my dear?</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: As Kirk and Mulhall double over, McCoy dashes to Spock's side, ready to inject him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Fortunately, Doctor, I know every thought of every mind around me. See? (to Chapel) Take the hypo from him. And inject him with it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: But she injects Spock/Henoch instead! He leaps from his seat.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Fools. I'll simply transfer to another place, another body.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He whirls around.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Sargon! No, Sargon, please. Let me. Let me transfer.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He falls to the floor and his victims are freed from their pain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>KIRK:  Spock. My friend Spock. If there'd only been another way.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>SARGON [OC]:  I could not allow your sacrifice of one so close to you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Lights dim and glow, then Chapel wobbles.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock stands up.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>KIRK:  You're alive.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>MCCOY:  There was enough poison in that hypo to kill ten Vulcans.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>SARGON [OC]:  No, Doctor. I allowed you to believe that to be true so that Henoch would read your thoughts and believe it also.</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Sargon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>SPOCK:  It seems, Doctor, the injection was only enough to cause unconsciousness.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>SARGON [OC]:  But Henoch believed and fled the body. He is destroyed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>KIRK:  But your vessel was destroyed, too. Where was your consciousness kept?</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The place Henoch would least suspect, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>CHAPEL:  That is why I was summoned into Sickbay, Doctor. Mister Spock's consciousness was placed in me. We shared consciousness together.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>SARGON [OC]:  We now know we cannot permit ourselves to exist in your world, my children. Thalassa and I must now also depart into oblivion.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>KIRK:  Is there any way we can help you, Sargon?</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>SARGON:  Yes, my son. You can allow Thalassa and me to share your bodies again. A last moment together.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Mulhall nods, and they go over to the science station for the light trick and voice change.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Oblivion together does not frighten me, beloved. Promise we'll be together.</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>KIRK:  I promise, beloved.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Together forever.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>KIRK:  Forever beloved. Forever.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They embrace and kiss, and the light thing happens again during it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, I'm sure that Sargon appreciated your co-operation, Doctor Mulhall.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>MULHALL:  Yes. I was happy to co-operate, Captain.</td></tr>

